This paper deals with the verification of hardware designs to eliminate timing side channels, which is a crucial aspect of cryptography. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves the use of clock precision and constant-time execution, which falls under the categories of cs.AR (Architecture) and cs.SE (Software Engineering). Additionally, the paper presents a new approach to verifying hardware designs, which could be relevant to the categories of cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science).
